ead rather than jumping in with no context.</p>\n<h2>Chapter and Line Skipping</h2>\n<p>Bookshelf lets you skip forward and backward a few lines or whole chapters in the book you are reading and even select the exact chapter you want to read.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/s5JGU57.png\"></p>\n<h2>Phrase/Word Search</h2>\n<p>Are you looking for a famous passage in your book? Perhaps you want to find the phrase you were trying to remember. Or maybe you just want to find every time Edward Cullen’s full name is mentioned. Just use Bookshelf’s search function to pull up all instances of the search term in moments and easily jump to the exact location you want in the book and continue readIng from there. </p>\n<p>Happy Reading!!!\n<img alt=\"iOS13\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/kpoXlNs.jpg\"></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://routinehub.co/user/robric18\"><img alt=\"created by robric18\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/SxFga7E.png\"></a></p>\n<p>Graphics made with <a href=\"https://routinehub.co/shortcut/1911\">MediaKit</a>.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>0.22 - Aug. 4, 2020, 4:48 p.m.</strong></p><p>Updated to include better Siri interface operation.</p>"}